**[1871, 01-24] Ms.A.9.2.32.79**

RDW to May Jr. English politics; Franco-Prussian War.

Forwards a speech by the MP for Halifax, [Stansfeld?], “a warm friend of
Mazzini & Garibaldi” and “an advanced Radical.” “I abhor this war & read
as little war news as I can help. … This war is to push back
civilization in Europe 100 years & whenever the poor people can they
will flock to the United States & perhaps perpetuate National hatreds
there.” Singles out German barbarities in particular. Allen has shown
him photographs of war-ravaged towns in Europe. “What seeds of national
hatred are sown for generations to come.”


